Introduction

TARGET is a seven-member boy group formed by TNS Entertainment. They first debuted in Japan on December 20, 2017, with the single "Atsui Omoi" and made their Korean debut on January 24, 2018, with the mini-album Alive.

as of July 2023, it is suspected that Seulchan has left Target and the company as he's now a member of Xeed from Nature Space. It's also suspected that sometime in 2021 both Woojin and Boun has left Target. Boun made his solo debut with his digital single "One Self" on April 22, 2022. Fans suspect that Woojin has left the group as he unfollowed everything Target and does not mention them.

The status of the group and the remaining members is unknown as their social media accounts haven't been active for at least 2 years. It is presumed they have disbanded as G.I will be part of a new group.
